         <abstract id="aspace_3999128bacf9f274b29b19aa25d34fe4">Joseph Ingram Sr. was a member of
            the Ingram family of Anson County, North Carolina. The collection contains family and
            business papers and correspondence of Joseph Ingram, Dr. E. N. Ingram, and various
            members of the Ingram family. The bulk of the collection belongs to the first half of
            the nineteenth century, and includes materials pertaining to the cotton industry,
            slavery, transportation, and social and economic conditions in Anson County, North
            Carolina.</abstract>
