      <scopecontent id="aspace_0456892ccbfbdec3b3e88dc61a72d498">
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         <p>The collection contains family and business papers and correspondence of Joseph Ingram,
            Dr. E. N. Ingram, and various members of the Ingram family. The bulk of the collection
            belongs to the first half of the nineteenth century, and includes materials referring to
            the cotton industry, slavery, transportation, and social and economic conditions in
            Anson County, North Carolina.</p>
      </scopecontent>
